I thought about this a little more and think that the API could be kept consistent with the existing design while achieving the desired effect with something like the following:
```
class ResourceCollection(object):
    def resumable_pages()
         return ResumablePage(self)
...

class ResumablePage(object)

    def __init__(self, collection):
        self.collection = collection

    @property
    def resume_token(self):
        # obtain and return token
        return token

    def __iter__(self):
        for item in self.collection:
           yield item
```

This would allow the general boto3 usage pattern to be maintained:
```
results = boto3.resource('ec2').instances.filter(NextToken='abc').page_size(10).resumable_pages()
print(results.resume_token)
print(results)
```

