@apli That sounds kind of like it might be stalling in DNS lookups (unrelated to dns_lookup_kdc or dns_lookup_realm).

When you're doing the testing, are you using the same inputs every time? If you are seeing wide variance with the same inputs, I would be looking towards things like DNS record TTLs or maybe kerberos ticket lifetime. One thing you could do is watch for DNS requests (using tcpdump or whatever) to see if there are external DNS queries that align with the slow calls. An occasionally slow external resolver (or congested network along the path to it) could result in this sort of behavior. Also I'm reading some stuff about gss_import_name that suggests that if the form of the input is such that a hostname is expected, and is absent, the local host is used. Sometimes machines have multiple DNS entries (perhaps via /etc/hosts) for 'localhost'. Maybe one of them resolves to an IPv6 address, but some portion of your stack is not v6 capable.

By the same token (heyo, kerberos puns), an external KDC may be occasionally slow in granting a TGT, or any other network interaction for that matter - but if so I wouldn't expect that slowness to show up under gss_import_name.

